pageType: content
background:
  type: solid
  color: "$background"
elements:
  - elementId: top-bar
    elementType: shape
    bounds: [0, 0, 1280, 6]
    shapeName: rect
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "$primary"
  - elementId: title
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 18, 1100, 38]
    content:
      style: "$actionTitle"
      align: [left, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>Retrain Models on Post-Shift Data and Reallocate Budget to High-ROAS Channels</p>
  - elementId: divider
    elementType: shape
    bounds: [60, 58, 1160, 1]
    shapeName: rect
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "$border"
  - elementId: left-header
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 72, 540, 30]
    content:
      style: "$sectionHeader"
      align: [left, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>Priority 1: Address Structural Shifts</p>
  - elementId: left-content
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 108, 540, 250]
    content:
      fontSize: 15
      color: "$text"
      fontFamily: "Liter"
      lineHeight: 1.5
      align: [left, top]
      text: |
        <p>18+ grains show test-period means &gt;2× training means, indicating a Feb 2026 regime change. The model is systematically underforecasting post-shift revenue.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:8px"><strong>Action:</strong> Retrain models with post-Feb 2026 data. Add a "regime" indicator feature to capture the structural shift.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:8px"><strong>Top affected grains:</strong></p>
        <p>• Shopping 60d: 24.1x train→test ratio</p>
        <p>• Meta Ads 60d: 5.2x ratio</p>
        <p>• Search 60d: 4.1x ratio</p>
        <p>• Google Ads 60d: 3.9x ratio</p>
  - elementId: right-header
    elementType: text
    bounds: [640, 72, 580, 30]
    content:
      style: "$sectionHeader"
      align: [left, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>Priority 2: Budget Reallocation</p>
  - elementId: right-table
    elementType: table
    bounds: [640, 108, 580, 250]
    columnWidths: [0.22, 0.15, 0.20, 0.43]
    rowHeights: [0.18, 0.16, 0.16, 0.16, 0.16, 0.18]
    style: "$default"
    rows:
      - - content: {text: "Channel"}
        - content: {text: "Action"}
        - content: {text: "Daily Spend"}
        - content: {text: "Rationale"}
      - - content: {text: "Search"}
        - content: {text: "Increase"}
        - content: {text: "$463 → $1K"}
        - content: {text: "10.3x ROAS, highest performer"}
      - - content: {text: "Bing Ads"}
        - content: {text: "Increase"}
        - content: {text: "$44 → $300"}
        - content: {text: "6.3x ROAS, untapped"}
      - - content: {text: "Meta 30d"}
        - content: {text: "Increase"}
        - content: {text: "$221 → $500"}
        - content: {text: "5.0x ROAS, room to scale"}
      - - content: {text: "Pmax"}
        - content: {text: "Decrease"}
        - content: {text: "$1K → $500"}
        - content: {text: "1.3x ROAS, near saturation"}
      - - content: {text: "Google 90d"}
        - content: {text: "Decrease"}
        - content: {text: "$2K → $1K"}
        - content: {text: "1.5x ROAS, declining"}
  - elementId: bottom-insight
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 375, 1160, 305]
    content:
      fontSize: 16
      color: "$text"
      fontFamily: "Liter"
      lineHeight: 1.5
      align: [left, top]
      text: |
        <p><strong>Expected Portfolio Impact:</strong> Reallocating $500 from Pmax to Bing Ads and Search could improve blended portfolio ROAS from 2.8x to 4.5x while maintaining total daily spend at ~$3,700. The structural shift means pre-Feb models are unreliable; retraining is essential before scaling any channel.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:10px"><strong>Implementation Notes:</strong></p>
        <p>• Search increase: Test in $100 increments weekly; monitor ROAS decay curve</p>
        <p>• Bing Ads increase: Scale to $300 over 4 weeks; test creative variations</p>
        <p>• Pmax decrease: Reduce by 25% weekly to avoid algorithm shock; redirect to Search</p>
        <p>• Google 90d decrease: Shift long-horizon budget to H30/H60 where ROAS is higher</p>
        <p style="margin-top:10px"><strong>Risk Factors:</strong> The Feb 2026 regime change means all historical response curves may be invalid. Budget reallocation should be paired with aggressive A/B testing and weekly forecast refreshes.</p>
  - elementId: source
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 692, 1100, 18]
    content:
      style: "$caption"
      align: [left, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>Source: AIgnition Stage 5 Budget Simulation and Stage 4 Forecast Validation</p>
  - elementId: page-num
    elementType: text
    bounds: [1170, 692, 50, 18]
    content:
      style: "$caption"
      align: [right, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>12</p>
